Issue: My pendrive was 28gb but it was showing 405kb free out of 405kb.


Link to guide: https://www.eassos.com/blog/how-to-restore-usb-drive-back-to-full-capacity/

Used tool: Command prompt as admin

Resolved issue via following steps::
a) diskpart

b) list disk

c) select disk 1      > here 1 is number of pendrive 

d) clear

e) create partition primary

f) format fs=fat32 quick
